SIMPLE: debilitate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Debilitate
<hw>De*bil"i*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Debilitated</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Debilitating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>debilitatus</ets>,
p. p. of <ets>debilitare</ets> to debilitate, fr. <ets>debilis</ets>.
See <er>Debility</er>.]</ety> <def>To impair the strength of; to weaken;
to enfeeble; <as>as, to <ex>debilitate</ex> the body by
intemperance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Various ails <qex>debilitate</qex> the mind.</q>
<rj><qau>Jenyns.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>debilitated</qex> frame of Mr. Bertram was exhausted by
this last effort.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>debilitated</ent>⟦br⟧
